value.0: With gear suited to the cold and frozen surroundings, these well trained and keen eyed rangers look as though they would be able to almost disappear into the wild when needed. Acting as the eyes and ears of Howness, as well as the first line of defense, they are all dedicated to protecting the town and its inhabitants from whatever may threaten.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.
The guardsmen of Howness. Outfitted with fresh and good looking steel, these men and women look well prepared to deal with any issues that arise in their town.

Predatory blue eyes keep careful watch on the surroundings, including you. One could not easily mistake this wolf for a dog. However, unlike its brethren which stalk the wilds this one seems to have been domesticated. While the guards of Howness have found a way to domesticate the wild wolves, it seems unlikely they would take as kindly to outsiders.
A black barrel - made of stone and reinforced with metal bands - a simple and cheap storage solution.
